### Application of the IUCN RLE criteria and categories

Data availability to assess all the criteria differs per realm. Therefore, the following criteria were assessed in each case (@tbl-applied-criteria). Broadly speaking, each realm assessment evaluated ecosystem types that are at risk of collapse because of habitat loss (A), because they are small in extent and declining in ecological condition (B), or because of declining ecological condition in their abiotic and/or biotic components (C, D). Criterion E is currently assessed as Data Deficient (DD) in all realms.


